  "prompt": "I have two year of work experience now I want to switch the job . Is there any written test as I give it during my campus recruitment for switching .",
  "response": "When switching jobs after two years of work experience, the recruitment process can vary depending on the company and industry. Here's a general overview:\n\nTypical Recruitment Process:\n1. Written Tests (Less Common)\n- Not as standard as campus recruitment\n- Some IT/tech companies might still conduct written tests\n- Mostly for technical roles or specific skill assessments\n\n2. More Common Screening Methods:\n- Resume/Profile screening\n- Technical/skill interviews\n- HR interviews\n- Coding assessments (for tech roles)\n- Background verification\n- Portfolio/project evaluation\n\n3. Interview Rounds\n- Usually 2-3 rounds\n- Technical round\n- HR round\n- Management/team fit round\n\n4. Alternative Assessment Methods:\n- Online coding platforms\n- Technical assignments\n- Problem-solving challenges\n- Skill-specific tests\n\n5. Preparation Recommendations:\n- Update resume\n- Refresh technical skills\n- Practice interview questions\n- Build professional network\n- Prepare portfolio/project documentation\n\nTips:\n- Focus on skill development\n- Target roles matching your experience\n- Use professional networking platforms\n- Prepare for different recruitment approaches\n\nRemember: Recruitment processes vary widely across companies and industries.",
